---
// File: src/pages/for-parents.astro
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="ZiiU — For Parents">
  <div class="kicker">For Parents</div>
  <h1>Support growth—without replacing parenting.</h1>
  <p>
    ZiiU helps students build self-awareness, healthy routines, and better decision-making.
    It’s designed to be safe, structured, and age-appropriate—so families can feel confident.
  </p>

  <div class="grid">
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Safety by Design</h3>
      <p>Guardrails, moderation, and age-aware guidance. ZiiU is built for youth from the start.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Privacy & Trust</h3>
      <p>No ads. No selling personal data. Data minimization and security-first practices.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Healthy Development</h3>
      <p>Focus on habits, resilience, and clarity—without pushing labels or creating dependence.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:22px;">
    <h3>What parents typically ask</h3>
    <p style="margin:0;">
      <strong>Is this therapy?</strong> No. ZiiU is a structured self-growth tool.<br />
      <strong>Is it social media?</strong> No. ZiiU does not rely on feeds or public posting.<br />
      <strong>How is safety handled?</strong> Through guardrails, content moderation, and careful design.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:16px;">
    <h3>Parent-first transparency</h3>
    <p style="margin:0;">
      ZiiU is being built with a clear privacy approach, optional parent resources, and
      age-appropriate experiences. As ZiiU expands, parents will have access to guidance
      on how to support healthy use.
    </p>
  </div>

  <p style="margin-top:18px; display:flex; gap:12px; flex-wrap:wrap;">
    <a class="btn primary" href="/get">Join Early Access</a>
    <a class="btn ghost" href="/for-schools">For schools & programs</a>
  </p>

  <p style="margin-top:10px; font-size:14px; color:#486175;">
    If you’re exploring ZiiU for a school program or pilot, visit the Schools page for partnership information.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
